<h2>Samsung Galaxy Ring — Best for Android</h2>
<img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1434494878577-86c23bcb06b9?w=800&q=80" alt="Samsung Galaxy Ring technology" style="width:100%;border-radius:10px;aspect-ratio:16/9;object-fit:cover;margin-bottom:20px;" loading="lazy"/>
<p>The Samsung Galaxy Ring integrates seamlessly with Samsung Health and Galaxy Watch. If you already have Samsung devices, data synergy is its biggest advantage. Sleep analysis is solid though it doesn't reach Oura's level, and battery lasts 7 days.</p>
<div class="pros-cons">
  <div class="pros-box"><span class="pros-box__label">✓ PROS</span><ul><li>No monthly subscription</li><li>Seamless Samsung integration</li><li>7-day battery</li></ul></div>
  <div class="cons-box"><span class="cons-box__label">✗ CONS</span><ul><li>Android only</li><li>Less accurate than Oura for HRV</li></ul></div>
</div>
<a href="https://www.samsung.com/us/smartphones/galaxy-ring/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="cta-btn" style="display:inline-block;margin-bottom:28px;">Check Samsung Galaxy Ring price →</a>
<h2>Ultrahuman Ring Air — Best for iPhone</h2>
<p>The Ultrahuman Ring Air is the most recommendable no-subscription alternative for iPhone users. Its app is well-designed, sleep analysis is accurate, and it's the lightest ring on the market (2.4 grams). It doesn't reach Oura's HRV level, but for most users the difference isn't noticeable.</p>
<div class="pros-cons">
  <div class="pros-box"><span class="pros-box__label">✓ PROS</span><ul><li>Compatible with iOS and Android</li><li>Lightest on the market</li><li>No subscription</li></ul></div>
  <div class="cons-box"><span class="cons-box__label">✗ CONS</span><ul><li>HRV less accurate than Oura</li><li>App less polished than Samsung</li></ul></div>
</div>
<a href="https://www.ultrahuman.com/ring" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="cta-btn" style="display:inline-block;margin-bottom:28px;">Check Ultrahuman Ring Air price →</a>
<h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>
<div class="faq-item" itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
  <p class="faq-item__q" itemprop="name">Is Oura Ring's subscription worth paying?</p>
  <div class="faq-item__a" itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
    <p itemprop="text">It depends on your use. If you want deep insights and personalized recommendations, yes. If you just want to see sleep and activity data, no-subscription alternatives are sufficient.</p>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="faq-item" itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
  <p class="faq-item__q" itemprop="name">Will Samsung Galaxy Ring ever work with iPhone?</p>
  <div class="faq-item__a" itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
    <p itemprop="text">No confirmed plans. Samsung has stated Galaxy Ring is designed for the Android/Samsung ecosystem. For iPhone, Ultrahuman or Oura are better options.</p>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="faq-item" itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
  <p class="faq-item__q" itemprop="name">Are there cheap smart rings that actually work?</p>
  <div class="faq-item__a" itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
    <p itemprop="text">The RingConn Gen 2 Air at around $149 offers decent tracking with no subscription. It's not as accurate as the others but it's an affordable entry into the smart ring world.</p>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="faq-item" itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
  <p class="faq-item__q" itemprop="name">How much do you save per year by choosing no-subscription?</p>
  <div class="faq-item__a" itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
    <p itemprop="text">Oura Ring costs $349 + $72/year = $421 the first year. Samsung Galaxy Ring is $299 one-time. Over 3 years the difference exceeds $210.</p>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="faq-item" itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
  <p class="faq-item__q" itemprop="name">Do the alternatives get software updates over time?</p>
  <div class="faq-item__a" itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
    <p itemprop="text">Yes, all update their app and algorithms. Samsung and Ultrahuman release regular software updates that improve features at no additional cost.</p>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="faq-item" itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
  <p class="faq-item__q" itemprop="name">Where to buy these alternatives in the US?</p>
  <div class="faq-item__a" itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
    <p itemprop="text">Samsung Galaxy Ring on samsung.com/us, Best Buy and Amazon. Ultrahuman Ring Air on ultrahuman.com. RingConn on ringconn.com with international shipping.</p>
